image.caption: Left to right, Oregon's, Lexi Bando, Oti Gildon, Maite Cazorla, Sabrina Ionescu and Justine Hall celebrate their 88-45 win over Seattle in the first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu (left) sores and is fouled by the Seattle Redhawks Madeline Dopplick during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu and Maite Cazorla, 5, get big on defenses in front of Seattle's Alexis Montgomery during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Aina Ayuso scores on the reverse layup and is fouled by Seattle Redhawks Joana Alves during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu who had a triple-double during the Duck's 88-45 win over Seattle drives by the Redhawks Madeline Dopplick during the second half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu (center) splits Seattle defenders Alexis Montgomery (left) and Kamira Sanders during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard, 24, who had contests Settles Kamira Sanders shot during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Lexi Bando who had 11 points on the night drives around Seattle defenders during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Justine Hall (center) comes up with the loose ball after forcing Seattle's Kamira Sanders (left) and Madeline Dopplick to fumble during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard scores between Seattle defenders Kallin Spiller (left) and Ashlyn Lewey during the first half in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's women's head basketball coach, Kelly Graves, claps after the Ducks downed the Redhawks 88-45 in a first-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Friday, March 16, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
